    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-01-10T09:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-01-10T09:00:00-05:00" n="244"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d244">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 657.119/231</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Norway</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_SAG1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Schmedeman</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Christiania</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-01-10T15:00:00+01:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 10, 1918—3 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received 5.25 p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>455. Sent note to Foreign Office yesterday in the sense of your telegram No. 201,
                    January 4, 7 p.m. British Minister has done likewise. London informed.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_SAG1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Schmedeman</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
